    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-09-23T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-09-23T18:00:00-05:00" n="411"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d411">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/4000: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-09-23T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 23, 1933—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>297. My 294, September 22, 11 p.m. The interview of Batista with the opposition
                    leaders was postponed until 3 o’clock this afternoon. The students have learned
                    of it and have insisted upon being present.</p>
                <p>I have very little hope of any agreement being reached owing to the interposition
                    of the Student Council. The latter at half past 2 o’clock this morning issued a
                    statement rejecting all compromise insisting that patriotic Cubans should
                    support the present government and making it very plain that the students
                    themselves and no others are the government.</p>
                <p>Owing to peremptory orders issued by the political leaders here last night a halt
                    was called to the revolutionary movement in Matanzas Province. The
                    revolutionists, however, have retained their arms and are awaiting
                    developments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
